data.title: Sean Penn's brother found dead
data.meta_description: Actor Chris Penn, the younger brother of actor Sean Penn, has died in California. Reports say he was found dead at his home in Santa Monica. Police say there are no signs of foul play
data.text:
Actor Chris Penn, the younger brother of actor Sean Penn, has died in California.

Reports say he was found dead at his home in Santa Monica. Police say there are no signs of foul play.

Film credits

Penn, 43, starred in dozens of films, including Quentin Tarantino's Reservoir Dogs, in which he played baby-faced criminal Nice Guy Eddie Cabot.

Other credits include Close Range and Footloose in 1984, in which he played Willard Hewitt.

More recently, Penn voiced Officer Eddie Pulaski in the video game Grand Theft Auto: San Andreas. His latest film, "The Darwin Awards," was scheduled to premiere at the Sundance Film Festival.

Sean Penn's publicist, Mara Buxbaum, issued a statement saying that "the Penn family would appreciate the media's respect of their privacy during this difficult time."
